news.title: Bombay HC clears way for Vienna Apartments to form independent housing society
news.para: The Bombay High Court has overturned a Maharashtra government decision blocking the Vienna Apartments Co-operative Housing Society in Juhu. The court ruled the refusal was legally incorrect and against homebuyer protection laws. An earlier approval from 2020 is now reinstated. Authorities must issue the registration certificate within four weeks.

news.title: Bombay HC rules CIDCO’s 22.5% land return scheme optional, not mandatory
news.para: The Bombay High Court has ruled CIDCO's 22.5% developed land return scheme is optional, not mandatory, for landowners. If landowners refuse the scheme, CIDCO must follow due process under the LARR Act and MRTP Act for acquisition, including full monetary compensation. This decision impacts land acquisition practices in Navi Mumbai and beyond.

news.title: Maharashtra: Panel suggests membership cancellation for flat owners blocking self-redevelopment
news.para: Flat owners who repeatedly obstruct self-redevelopment projects after legal challenges fail could lose their society membership. A state-appointed study group proposes this measure. If over 51% of society members approve a redevelopment plan, it will be binding. Dissenting members must vacate their homes. If they refuse, authorities may evict them.

news.title: Mumbai civic body to conduct first independent online lottery for sale of affordable flats
news.para: The Brihanmumbai Municipal Corporation will conduct its first independent online lottery for 426 homes. These flats are located across Mumbai and are priced between Rs 55 lakh and Rs 1 crore. Only applicants from Economically Weaker Section and Low-Income Group categories are eligible. This initiative is expected to generate Rs 308 crore for the civic body.

news.title: Cash-strapped railways looks to lease out Mumbai land worth thousands of crores
news.para: Strapped for funds, the Indian Railways is leasing prime land in Mumbai and other metros to private developers. After missing its first monetisation target by over Rs 1.2 lakh crore, it now hopes to unlock billions through 99-year leases

news.title: Auction purchasers liable to pay property tax dues: Calcutta HC
news.para: The Calcutta High Court ruled that auction purchasers are liable for outstanding property tax dues of previous owners. A company seeking property mutation was denied by KMC due to over Rs 1.2 crore in arrears accumulated by the former owner. The court emphasized that bidders are expected to conduct their own due diligence.

news.title: Mahindra Logistics leases 4.75 lakh sq ft warehouse in Kolkata
news.para: Mahindra Logistics is expanding its presence in eastern India. The company has leased a large warehousing space in Howrah, near Kolkata. This move will boost its services across West Bengal, Jharkhand, Odisha, and the Northeast. Eastern India is becoming a key logistics hub due to improved infrastructure and growing demand.

news.title: H-RERA adds one more member, restored quorum to help expedite case disposal in Gurugram
news.para: Haryana Real Estate Regulatory Authority (HRera) has regained its full strength with the induction of Phool Singh Saini as its fourth member. This appointment fills a vacancy and restores the complete quorum, aiming to ensure faster disposal of homebuyers' complaints. Saini's judicial experience is expected to bolster HRera's functioning in handling disputes against developers.

news.title: Consumer groups urge MahaRERA to regulate real estate influencers
news.para: Consumer groups are urging MahaRERA to regulate real estate influencers who promote housing projects without verifying registration numbers, leaving homebuyers vulnerable. Experts emphasize influencers' role in decision-making and call for a structured framework, drawing parallels to SEBI's regulation of financial influencers. MahaRERA acknowledges the difficulty but deems it essential for ensuring homebuyers receive reliable information.

news.title: YEIDA reclaims 300 acres land in Aligarh
news.para: Yamuna Expressway Industrial Development Authority (YEIDA) has reclaimed 300 acres of land valued at Rs 1,200 crore in Aligarh district. This action followed a massive demolition and anti-encroachment operation against illegal colonies. YEIDA is intensifying its crackdown on unauthorized developers and fraudulent land sales, especially near the upcoming Noida International Airport.

news.title: Maharashtra: Only 31% recovery warrants against builders executed, homebuyers irked
news.para: Homebuyers in Maharashtra are facing significant delays in recovering funds from errant builders, with only 31% of recovery warrants executed. Despite government directives and appointments of additional officials, a substantial backlog persists, leaving buyers waiting years for refunds and causing immense stress.

news.title: Builders eye regulatory clarity from RERA as Andhra Pradesh witnesses real estate revival
news.para: Andhra Pradesh's real estate sector is experiencing a revival, with Rera playing a crucial role in ensuring transparency and protecting stakeholders. Developers are awaiting Rera's resolution of technical hurdles to expedite project completion, expecting further market growth. The strict implementation of the Real Estate Act is boosting buyer confidence and driving planned urban expansion.

news.title: Bengaluru authority launches one-time scheme to convert B-khata properties to A-khata
news.para: Bengaluru property owners can now convert B-khata properties to A-khata. A one-time settlement scheme offers this opportunity for eligible sites. This initiative aims to regularize properties and clean up the market.

news.title: Oberoi Realty's profit rises 29% to ₹760.26 crore in Q2 FY26
news.para: Oberoi Realty has announced a significant 29 percent jump in its consolidated profit for the second quarter of this fiscal year. The company's profit reached Rs 760.26 crore, up from Rs 589.44 crore in the same period last year.

news.title: Telangana government deposits ₹2,223 crore to Indiramma scheme beneficiaries
news.para: Telangana Housing Corporation has disbursed Rs 2,223 crore this year under the Indiramma housing scheme, with funds directly credited to beneficiaries' accounts based on construction progress. The government remains committed to providing timely financial support for the completion of approximately 2.18 lakh houses across the state.

news.title: Nuvoco Vistas posts net profit of ₹36.43 crore in Q2 FY26
news.para: Nuvoco Vistas Corp, the Nirma Group's building materials arm, posted a profit of Rs 36.43 crore in the second quarter. This marks a significant turnaround from a net loss in the same period last year. Revenue from operations saw an increase of 8.33 percent.

news.title: Kerala government expedites process to finalise land for IT corridor
news.para: Kerala government is set to finalize land for multiple IT parks along the Thiruvananthapuram-Kollam IT corridor within two months. The project, aiming to boost the region's tech ecosystem, will involve acquiring land for two or more parks and a 5 lakh sq ft facility in Kollam city.

news.title: Vasai-Virar ex-civic chief's arrest in money laundering case 'illegal', says HC; orders his release
news.para: The Bombay High Court has pronounced the Enforcement Directorate's detention of Anil Pawar, the former head of Vasai-Virar's civic body, to be unconstitutional. Prompted by the lack of credible evidence from the ED, the court mandated his swift release.

news.title: Embassy Group repays ₹1,748 crore debt
news.para: Embassy Group has successfully repaid ₹1,748 crore in non-convertible debentures, leveraging funds from the WeWork India IPO's offer for sale. This strategic move has significantly reduced group-level debt and lowered its stake in WeWork India to 15%, reinforcing the company's financial stability.

news.title: Kolte-Patil Developers' pre-sales down 13% at ₹670crore in Q2 FY26
news.para: In the second quarter, Kolte-Patil Developers reported a 13 percent decline in sales bookings, totaling Rs 670 crore, signaling a slowdown in the Indian residential market. This downturn is marked by reduced sales volumes compared to last year. However, there is optimism among builders, who are hopeful for a resurgence in demand as the festive season approaches.
